			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				O my lord...Ive read on how people turn in to @$%holes in this zone but me being the constant optimistic, learned<BR>
a hard lesson.  I'm in Highpass yesterday and I group up with 2 other people there to kill gnolls, now our main purpose was not to camp the PGT but while scouting out the area, we noticed <BR>
that there was not a single person in that area, I mean no where.  So<BR>
we were like cool if he spawns we can take him.  Well after about 10 mins<BR>
of killing the regular spawns, who else spawns but non other than the PGT wielding Gnoll himself.  So we set to taking him out.  After about 2 min<BR>
of wacking away on him, we notice all of a sudden some high lvl spells being cast upon him.  A min later he was dead and none of us could loot the body.  Come to find out a 20+ lvl Dark Elf caster came to claim &quot;her prize&quot;. She stated that she had been hidden the whole time<BR>
and had been camping there for 2 hours.  Now because she did not say anything we were all pretty pissed about it and began a lengthy arguement.  After that we just said o well and continued to fight gnolls.  Well low and behold, about 10-15min later, the PGT bearing<BR>
beast spawns again.  And guess what, the DE witch decides to zap it again.  And of course none of use can loot<BR>
it.  And on purpose, knowing that she could not hold two PGT at one time, looted the corpse right in front of us just so we could not get it.  Now I am the type of player that loves to help people in i believe in fair play, if someone was to get to some mob before I do, then i will let them have it no problem what so ever, I will even help them if they need it without any thought that the loot should be mine.  But this person has scarred me for a while i believe.  If im camping something I now fear that I cannot trust anyone that happens to come along and that<BR>
saddens greatly.  So folks, it does happen, even to fair honest folk that I know play out there.<BR>
Good luck.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
